        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 12 at 3:10PM MDT by NWS Bismarck ND</headline>
        <description>At 310 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles east of Mud Buttes, or 12 miles southwest of Bowman, moving
northeast at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Mud Buttes.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
